You can also do the same by specifying the width of the bins.

<pre class="mcode">
d <- ggplot(diamonds, aes(x, y)) + xlim(4, 10) + ylim(4, 10)
p <-  d + geom_bin_2d(binwidth = c(0.1, 0.1))

plotly::ggplotly(p)
</pre>
